guild is being chased around by pandemonium all day. Exp grops being destroyed and raids being destroyed also.... There is no chance in fighting back.- Bronkus</center><img src="http://eqvvv.org/images/noobiebeggers.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrettsc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>brettsc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/22/02 2:17:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1437.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Double Attack and Fast delay Weapons</span><hr size=1> &quot;The speed of the weapon does not matter much at lower levels. That is where the myth of ratio being king has come from. When your skill level in double attack is so low, you don't get to swing your offhand faster then the delay ever, so there is no reason to have a low delay. <br><br>However, when you get to 50s and up, the delay of the offhand is very important. I don't know where the break is (and I suppose it would be different for each delay) but the level is somewhere in the high 40s low 50s where the delay of the offhand becomes a big deal.&quot;<br><br><br>The way i though it worked was;<br>Offhand is totally independent of mainhand. <br>There is no damage bonus for the offhand. <br>The only logical time for a double attack skill check is when the offhand weapon refreshes.<br>Damage of the weapon determines how hard you hit.<br>Delay of the weapon determines how often you swing and DA check.<br>So, faster weapon = more swings, slower weapon = less swings, but harder hits.<br><br>I cant see any reason why a faster weapon is &gt; better ratio in offhand.<br><br><br>Wurms